Description: Afrikaans names are used by Afrikaans speakers in the countries of South Africa and Namibia.
African names are used on the continent of Africa, covering a wide number of languages.
Akan names are used by the Akan people of Ghana and Ivory Coast.
Albanian names are used in the country of Albania, as well as Kosovo and other Albanian communities throughout the world.
Algonquin names are used by the Algonquin people of Ontario and Quebec in Canada.
These names are or were used by the various indigenous peoples who inhabit North and South America.
Amharic names are used in Ethiopia.
These names were used in various ancient regions.
Apache names are used by the Apache peoples of the southwestern United States.

Arabic names are used in the Arab world, as well as some other regions within the larger Muslim world. They are not necessarily of Arabic origin, though most in fact are. Compare also Persian names and Turkish names.
Armenian names are used in the country of Armenia in western Asia, as well as in Armenian diaspora communities throughout the world.
Assamese names are used in Assam in eastern India.
Asturian names are used in Asturias in northern Spain by speakers of Asturian.

These names are used by the Mohawk (Kanienkehaka) people of New York, Ontario and Quebec. Mohawk children are traditionally given a name that is unique to their community, and it is not reused while the bearer is alive. It is considered inappropriate for outsiders to use these names.

Occitan names are used in southern France and parts of Spain and Italy by speakers of Occitan.
Odia or Oriya names are used in eastern India (in the state of Odisha).
